[{"client_msg_id":"de00f765-82fe-4564-bc90-e8572ecad05f","type":"message","text":"Out of curiosity I read <https://docs.julialang.org/en/v1.7-dev/NEWS/> and wonder why `findmax(f, array)` was chosen - instead of `maximum(array, by=f)` to be consistent with `sort(array, by=f)`. Linked issues don't have much background. Anyone familiar with this?","user":"UGTUKUHLN","ts":"1610405446.231900","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"x+CV","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Out of curiosity I read "},{"type":"link","url":"https://docs.julialang.org/en/v1.7-dev/NEWS/"},{"type":"text","text":" and wonder why "},{"type":"text","text":"findmax(f, array)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" was chosen - instead of "},{"type":"text","text":"maximum(array, by=f)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" to be consistent with "},{"type":"text","text":"sort(array, by=f)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":". Linked issues don't have much background. Anyone familiar with this?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","reply_count":78,"reply_users_count":5,"latest_reply":"1610414512.253200","reply_users":["UH8A351DJ","U8D9768Q6","UGTUKUHLN","U0179G7FG4F","U6A936746"],"subscribed":false},{"client_msg_id":"a63cb1ea-3767-4030-9179-3d05af22196b","type":"message","text":"this is to be consistent with `findfirst(==(3), [1,2,3])`","user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610405657.232000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"29PJ","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"this is to be consistent with "},{"type":"text","text":"findfirst(==(3), [1,2,3])","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"339cc9cf-12c9-4b19-b307-533abba57afd","type":"message","text":"it's part of the findX family if that helps","user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610405691.232200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"o1i","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"it's part of the findX family if that helps"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"62e0981f-a57e-430a-a14a-bc210745560f","type":"message","text":"And the reason that do that is for the `do` block notation:\n```julia&gt; findmax([1, 2, 3, 4]) do x\n           y = x^2 - 1\n           y == 3\n       end\n(true, 2)```","user":"U8D9768Q6","ts":"1610405813.232600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"lDt2","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"And the reason that do that is for the "},{"type":"text","text":"do","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" block notation:\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> findmax([1, 2, 3, 4]) do x\n           y = x^2 - 1\n           y == 3\n       end\n(true, 2)"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"719c85e3-bea9-4e2d-956e-655a8318c876","type":"message","text":"Well, `findfirst` is not really consistent here in what it returns :slightly_smiling_face:\n```julia&gt; findfirst(==(3), [1,2,3])\n3\n\njulia&gt; findmax(==(3), [1,2,3])\n(true, 3)```","user":"UGTUKUHLN","ts":"1610405815.232800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"t9b","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Well, "},{"type":"text","text":"findfirst","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is not really consistent here in what it returns "},{"type":"emoji","name":"slightly_smiling_face"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> findfirst(==(3), [1,2,3])\n3\n\njulia> findmax(==(3), [1,2,3])\n(true, 3)"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"cf4ed323-18e5-4213-8b1f-305b263949cc","type":"message","text":"Would the `do`-argument work the same way for `sort`?","user":"UGTUKUHLN","ts":"1610405840.233000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"nKo","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Would the "},{"type":"text","text":"do","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"-argument work the same way for "},{"type":"text","text":"sort","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"3c106c66-2e59-442a-b4df-d2d3e07318b5","type":"message","text":"no","user":"U8D9768Q6","ts":"1610405846.233200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"K7g","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"no"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"f1d20ab7-8d93-4300-b433-4b7c6535321f","type":"message","text":"just like `map` `do`, you need the anonymous function to be the first argument","user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610405866.233400","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610405871.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"IaQe","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"just like "},{"type":"text","text":"map","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"do","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":", you need the anonymous function to be the first argument"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"0c9f1978-2c6d-4613-88d8-e4602f93bdb3","type":"message","text":"I mean, not the function argument, but the general argument: \"why `sort` doesn't allow `do` notation\"","user":"UGTUKUHLN","ts":"1610405898.233700","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"SgjTU","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"I mean, not the function argument, but the general argument: \"why "},{"type":"text","text":"sort","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" doesn't allow "},{"type":"text","text":"do","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" notation\""}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"55e20890-ded0-41cd-b63c-2dcea26335bf","type":"message","text":"sorry for confusion","user":"UGTUKUHLN","ts":"1610405900.233900","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"XDZ","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"sorry for confusion"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"3215fe1e-8b9c-4fa3-a8de-e76ad4121466","type":"message","text":"what do you mean it's not consistent with findfirst? what you see is purly because findmax returns both the computed result and the index","user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610405937.234100","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"7Q/l","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"what do you mean it's not consistent with findfirst? what you see is purly because findmax returns both the computed result and the index"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"05d4a6e0-28f7-4b23-842a-a7ca41d2cb21","type":"message","text":"```julia&gt; findmax(1:3)\n(3, 3)```","user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610405939.234300","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"xUQ","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> findmax(1:3)\n(3, 3)"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"456d8054-8ca0-46d5-a086-61687eafe094","type":"message","text":"so you don't have to compute twice","user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610405946.234500","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"xNbjk","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"so you don't have to compute twice"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"01b8b462-659f-4bd5-97c5-93b708676dff","type":"message","text":"```idx = findmax(by_func, array)\nval = by_func(array[idx])```","user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610405970.234700","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610405976.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"y7dU","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"idx = findmax(by_func, array)\nval = by_func(array[idx])"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"7d526af9-4a87-47ad-a117-b3126cdcb6e9","type":"message","text":"yes, `findmax` retuns two values and `findfirst` only one\nthat's the inconsistency","user":"UGTUKUHLN","ts":"1610406002.235000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Xtw6s","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"yes, `findmax` retuns two values and `findfirst` only one\nthat's the inconsistency"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"4b3cb556-5501-4eae-a6a0-d2c3b7d38f48","type":"message","text":"that is the design. \"making things appears to be the same\" != consistency","user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610406028.235200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Dc/Jx","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"that is the design. \"making things appears to be the same\" != consistency"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"5b3cca66-d276-4a6d-8141-c9978d462bd7","type":"message","text":"He's not saying they're the same function, he's saying that family of functions all accept a function as their first argument for use with `do` blocks.","user":"U8D9768Q6","ts":"1610406048.235400","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"ulkp","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"He's not saying they're the same function, he's saying that family of functions all accept a function as their first argument for use with "},{"type":"text","text":"do","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" blocks."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"d86e1721-e5ac-4dfe-ae52-6a1c325d5753","type":"message","text":"sorry, right, I'm just saying, `findX(func, array)` is the calling convention, and that is where the consistency exist","user":"UH8A351DJ","ts":"1610406093.235600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"RngD","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"sorry, right, I'm just saying, "},{"type":"text","text":"findX(func, array)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is the calling convention, and that is where the consistency exist"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"f1eb431a-6df2-4d08-bb77-517f2cfeda5e","type":"message","text":"do you know whether these are mostly issues of legacy that cannot be changed in a compatible manner, or deliberate decisions? e.g., `findmax(f, A)` vs `sort(A, by=f)` ; `findmax -&gt; (val, ix)` vs `findfirst -&gt; ix`","user":"UGTUKUHLN","ts":"1610406159.235800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"XHRu","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"do you know whether these are mostly issues of legacy that cannot be changed in a compatible manner, or deliberate decisions? e.g., "},{"type":"text","text":"findmax(f, A)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" vs "},{"type":"text","text":"sort(A, by=f)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" ; "},{"type":"text","text":"findmax -> (val, ix)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" vs "},{"type":"text","text":"findfirst -> ix","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1610405446.231900","parent_user_id":"UGTUKUHLN"},{"client_msg_id":"3b901318-ea30-4f28-8956-16a83c0ced05","type":"message","text